text: Jana Žitňanská (born 17 May 1974) is a Slovak politician. Since 2014 she has been a Member of the European Parliament, where she is a member of the European Conservatives and Reformists (ECR). She is also a journalist. ==References== Category:1974 births Category:Living people Category:People from Bratislava Category:New Majority (Slovakia) MEPs Category:Women MEPs for Slovakia Category:MEPs for Slovakia 2014–2019 Category:21st-century Slovak women politicians
